You can run a script.sh to check the driver

How does the script work step by step:

1) Module loading without parameters;

2) Displaying buffer size;

3) Writing "Hello, dev" to character device via /dev interface;

4) Displaying buffer size;

5) Reading from character device via /dev interface;

6) Displaying buffer size;

7) Module unloading;

8) Module loading with BUFFER_SIZE=1500";

9) Displaying buffer size;

10) Module unloading;

11) Module loading without parameters;

12) Writing "Hello, dev" to character device via /dev interface;

13) Displaying buffer size;

14) Cleaning buffer via /sysfs interface;

15) Displaying buffer size;

16) Module unloading;


